reviews.headline: It's a no from me.
reviews.comments: I was excited to try this product but I just can't get it to consistently work with my skin. When I apply it pills up and separates. I've gotten it to work a handful of times but its too much trouble for the price and never knowing HOW its going to look. I'm sad because I wanted to love it- but I'm definitely going to be returning it.

reviews.headline: Just in AWE
reviews.comments: 1st I want to say I haven't worn it out yet, but I did a little sample on the back of my hand & I'm literally blown away! I love their concealer so I thought it would match well, but never imagined it would be perfect! I did the "try on" feature with two different photos with the recommended shade & the shade i thought was best. Ultimately chose the one i was recommended & it's an absolute perfect match! I would rate 5 if I actually applied it to my face, but even though it's the back of my hand it's a perfect match!! Also, my skin feels smoother on the application side, it's not transferring onto my sheets, nor cellphone.

reviews.headline: Over this brand
reviews.comments: Used to love their products, still would if they wouldn't DISCONTINUE them without warning. Cant even leave a review on the products I did like because they dont exist anymore. I don't know how they expect to maintain brand loyalty if they can't even deliver a consistent product. Never had this problem before and I won't risk it again by continuing to use only Estee Lauder products. They are too expensive for that level of abysmal customer serivce.

faceoff_positive.comments:
ï»¿I received the Estee Lauder Futurist SkinTint Serum with Botanical Oil Infusion Broad Spectrum SPF20 as a free product in exchange for my honest review.  
To be honest I had no idea what a skin tint was. I thought at first it was a moisturizing cream with color added. Much to my surprise this is a completely different kind of product. 
When asked what color I wanted to try I chose 1N1 Ivory Nude. I thought I would try and pick the color closest to my skin color.  
The product comes in a beautiful glass rectangular bottle with a dropper on the top and of course the beautiful packaging you receive with all Estee Lauder products. 
I shook the bottle prior to usage. 
The consistency resembles an opaque thinner foundation.
The purpose of this product is to apply it previous to going out in the sun, because it has the SPF20 rather than applying the traditional foundation. 
I applied it all over my face and much to my surprise it made my face a VERY LIGHT COLOR!
It is much unlike any product I have previously used. In spite of me applying my foundation over it, it still turned my face lighter! In addition, it helped with wrinkles! 
For those of you looking for a lighter skin tone, THIS IS THE PRODUCT FOR YOU in this color. 
Had I have known how this product worked and how potent it is, I would have asked for a darker color; however, I decided to use it in a different way. I applied this product under my eyes and THE DARKNESS UNDER MY EYES WENT AWAY! This is FANTASTIC for using as a concealer under your eyes! I applied concealer over it and it is absolutely BEAUTIFUL! 
Perhaps this product was not made for this purpose, but I absolutely LOVE IT! I no longer have to apply a ton of concealer when trying to cover up the darkness under my eyes. 
For those of you looking for a tanned effect, buy the darker colors, because this product is not going to cake up on your face like some other foundation might. 
The product contains Octinoxate 6.7%, Octisalate 4.5%, Zinc Oxide 6.8%
faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing Product with multiple uses

faceoff_negative.comments:
I like this but I don't love it. I typically go for a lighter coverage base so this sounded like something that I would really enjoy because it claims to have light coverage with a natural finish and feel lightweight on the skin. I completely agree that it feels lightweight because it does have a very serum-like consistency and it absolutely provides light coverage - I really don't feel like it's possible to build this up very much without it looking heavy and overdone - - but it definitely has a very luminous finish rather than a natural finish.
I have dry skin and even I feel like this looks a little too glowy for my taste. This definitely begs for powder, not only to tone down the shine a bit but also to set the tint into place because it won't completely set on its own.  Because it's very radiant, it can definitely tend to emphasize texture and therefore I don't think that people with extremely oily skin as well as people who feel very self-conscious about any texture / fine lines that they may have will necessarily enjoy this very much. For this to look and where it's best, I typically apply a smoothing or blurring primer, apply the tint with a brush in order to maximize coverage without building it up too much, and set it into place with a loose powder to help mattify and blur its appearance. I can definitely make it look nice but I feel like it's a little bit of a finicky product and for the price tag I feel like it shouldn't require quite that much effort. I'm not going to recommend against trying this because I do think it's possible to achieve a really pretty end result but that being said, I think that there are other options that require less work.
